libshout
------------------------------------------
Libshout is a library for communicating with and sending data to an
icecast server.  It handles the socket connection, the timing of the
data, and prevents bad data from getting to the icecast server.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  libogg0-1.1.2-1
  libspeex1-1.1.10-1
  libtheora0-1.0alpha7-1
  libvorbis0-1.1.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.2.11-1
  gawk-3.1.5-4
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  libtool1.5-1.5.24a-2
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.21-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.icecast.org/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.us.xiph.org/releases/libshout/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libshout-2.2.2-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libshout-2.2.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libshout-2.2.2-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libshout-2.2.2-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libshout3-2.2.2-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary packages:

(libshout)
  /usr/include/shout/shout.h
  /usr/lib/libshout.a
  /usr/lib/libshout.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libshout.la
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/shout.pc
  /usr/share/aclocal/shout.m4
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libshout-2.2.2.README
  /usr/share/doc/libshout-2.2.2/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libshout-2.2.2/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/libshout-2.2.2/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libshout-2.2.2/README
  /usr/share/doc/libshout-2.2.2/example.c
  /usr/share/doc/libshout-2.2.2/nonblocking.c

(libshout3)
  /usr/bin/cygshout-3.dll

